Aztec first appeared on the 1920 U.S. Census as the Aztec Precinct of Yuma County.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Bureau of the Census Library |title=Fourteenth Census of the United States - State Compendium - Arizona |url=http://www2.census.gov/prod2/decennial/documents/06229686v1-7ch02.pdf |publisher=Government Printing Office |date=1924}}</ref> It appeared again in 1930, and recorded having a Spanish/Hispanic majority<ref>{{cite web |title=Arizona - Composition and Characteristics |url=https://www2.census.gov/prod2/decennial/documents/10612963v3p1ch02.pdf |website=United States Census Bureau |pages=141{{endash}}163 |date=1930}}</ref> (the census would not separately feature that racial demographic again until 1980). Aztec's population was 31 in 1940.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZTcjAQAAMAAJ |title=The Attorneys List |publisher=United States Fidelity and Guaranty Company, Attorney List Department |year=1940 |page=85 |language=en}}</ref> The population was 65 in the 1960 census.<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |year=1960 |title=Arizona |encyclopedia=[[World Book Encyclopedia]] |publisher=Field Enterprises Educational Corporation |location=Chicago |volume=A |page=557}}</ref> In 2010, it was made a census-designated place (CDP).

